1
00:00:42,659 --> 00:00:43,699
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

2
00:00:43,699 --> 00:00:44,753
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

3
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:45,770
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

4
00:00:45,770 --> 00:00:46,963
[under professional supervision.]

5
00:01:13,653 --> 00:01:15,999
<i>You</i>

6
00:01:15,999 --> 00:01:19,006
<i>just wanted to use me</i>

7
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:24,042
<i>for your grand ambition.</i>

8
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:31,404
<i>Do you get it now?</i>

9
00:01:31,404 --> 00:01:34,204
<i>This is your last chance.</i>

10
00:01:34,884 --> 00:01:37,684
<i>You choose.</i>

11
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,686
<i>Either you or me...</i>

12
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:47,149
<i>If this goes any further,</i>

13
00:01:48,099 --> 00:01:51,631
<i>it won't end with someone getting hurt.</i>

14
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:05,584
<i>I did everything I could to protect you,</i>

15
00:02:07,169 --> 00:02:10,631
<i>but maybe I chose the wrong way.</i>

16
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:08,361
[Danger: High Voltage]
[Authorized Personnel Only]

17
00:04:55,724 --> 00:04:58,424
<i>Mr. Bang Tae Seop.</i>

18
00:04:58,424 --> 00:05:01,060
<i>What you're about to do</i>

19
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:04,257
<i>is kill the dead a second time.</i>

20
00:05:08,452 --> 00:05:11,585
<i>But once you see this through,</i>

21
00:05:11,585 --> 00:05:13,336
<i>you'll rise all the way to the top,</i>

22
00:05:13,336 --> 00:05:16,842
<i>just like you wanted.</i>

23
00:05:18,664 --> 00:05:22,050
<i>But in return...</i>

24
00:05:24,295 --> 00:05:25,918
<i>You'll have to give up</i>

25
00:05:25,918 --> 00:05:29,791
<i>the one thing you value most.</i>

26
00:05:34,747 --> 00:05:37,441
<i>For example...</i>

27
00:05:44,023 --> 00:05:46,990
<i>Chu Sang Ah.</i>

28
00:05:52,338 --> 00:05:54,898
<i>Fine.</i>

29
00:05:55,758 --> 00:05:58,804
<i>Then I'll be the one who dies.</i>

30
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:15,092
[Episode 1]

31
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:25,302
<i>I was born the son of a factory worker.</i>

32
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,870
<i>My father was a union leader.</i>

33
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:30,164
<i>While fighting for the workers' rights,</i>

34
00:06:30,164 --> 00:06:31,960
<i>he was handed a prison sentence</i>

35
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:34,911
<i>by the prosecutor on the case,
a man who had taken bribes from the company.</i>

36
00:06:34,911 --> 00:06:36,257
[Steel Mill Union Leader Bang's Tragic Death:
Will the Truth Ever Come Out?]

37
00:06:36,257 --> 00:06:37,363
<i>And that night...</i>

38
00:06:37,363 --> 00:06:40,534
<i>he took his own life.</i>

39
00:06:46,116 --> 00:06:49,189
<i>I wanted revenge.</i>

40
00:06:53,471 --> 00:06:56,924
<i>That's why I became a prosecutor.</i>

41
00:06:56,924 --> 00:06:59,931
<i>But that place...</i>

42
00:06:59,931 --> 00:07:02,362
<i>was their own private kingdom.</i>

43
00:07:02,362 --> 00:07:03,902
[Stay strong today and tomorrow, too.]

44
00:07:08,278 --> 00:07:11,574
<i>To squeeze in among the bloodlines
that run the legal world,</i>

45
00:07:11,574 --> 00:07:13,001
<i>I even emptied my rent money</i>

46
00:07:13,001 --> 00:07:14,934
<i>to buy a Mercedes-benz,</i>

47
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:17,271
<i>and crashed at my sister's hair salon.</i>

48
00:07:17,271 --> 00:07:20,372
[Seong Hye Hair Salon]

49
00:07:24,778 --> 00:07:27,124
<i>I even tried getting in
with the chief prosecutor's circle.</i>

50
00:07:27,124 --> 00:07:28,715
<i>Once, I hung off</i>

51
00:07:28,715 --> 00:07:30,399
<i>a ninth-floor hotel railing</i>

52
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:34,680
<i>for five hours in eight-below-zero weather.</i>

53
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,547
<i>But nothing changed.</i>

54
00:07:41,793 --> 00:07:43,463
Come on.

55
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,248
Knock it off.

56
00:07:45,248 --> 00:07:48,841
You really think that'll get you in
with those true-blood elites?

57
00:07:48,841 --> 00:07:50,294
Well...

58
00:07:50,294 --> 00:07:51,818
The more desperate you are,

59
00:07:51,818 --> 00:07:53,878
the easier it is for them
to squeeze you dry and toss you aside.

60
00:07:53,878 --> 00:07:57,087
That's how the prosecution works.

61
00:07:57,087 --> 00:08:00,397
<i>I wanted to stand above the world</i>

62
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:03,687
<i>and look down on them.</i>

63
00:08:03,687 --> 00:08:05,971
<i>I needed the key</i>

64
00:08:05,971 --> 00:08:09,124
<i>that could open the gates to that kingdom.</i>

65
00:08:20,495 --> 00:08:23,215
<i>Chu Sang Ah.</i>

66
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:50,348
<i>In the end,</i>

67
00:08:50,348 --> 00:08:54,713
<i>I met her when she came in
for questioning as a witness.</i>

68
00:09:22,569 --> 00:09:26,055
<i>It was the perfect opportunity</i>

69
00:09:26,055 --> 00:09:28,493
<i>to make the world know my name.</i>

70
00:09:28,493 --> 00:09:30,117
[Top Actress Chu Sang Ah Announces Marriage]

71
00:09:30,117 --> 00:09:33,602
<i>The relationship between a dirt-poor prosecutor
and a pop star who once swept across Asia</i>

72
00:09:33,602 --> 00:09:35,066
<i>is being called
Korea's version of "Notting Hill,"</i>

73
00:09:35,066 --> 00:09:36,579
<i>a marriage of the century</i>

74
00:09:36,579 --> 00:09:41,039
<i>that has captured the nation
like a real-life romance drama.</i>

75
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:49,589
[Top Star Chu Sang Ah Suspected of
Multi-Billion-Won Tax Evasion]

76
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:52,127
[The Fall of the Nation's Actress]

77
00:09:52,127 --> 00:09:54,705
[Despite her heartfelt apology,
public reaction remains cold]

78
00:09:54,705 --> 00:09:56,582
<i>Today, we have someone,</i>

79
00:09:56,582 --> 00:09:59,536
<i>who has stood by my side for many years</i>

80
00:09:59,536 --> 00:10:02,150
[Chu Sang Ah After Tax Evasion Scandal]
<i>and endured this harsh industry with me.</i>

81
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:03,572
[Spotted at Co-CEO's Child's Birthday Party]
<i>Our nation's beloved actress.</i>

82
00:10:03,572 --> 00:10:07,126
<i>Please welcome Chu Sang Ah.</i>

83
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,584
<i>Come out here for a moment.</i>

84
00:10:13,584 --> 00:10:15,371
[She looks flustered]
<i>It's okay.</i>

85
00:10:15,371 --> 00:10:18,511
<i>Let's give her a round of applause.</i>

86
00:10:19,747 --> 00:10:21,712
<i>- Please sing a song for us.
- Please!</i>

87
00:10:21,712 --> 00:10:23,471
[She's aged a lot since we last saw her]
<i>Sing for us.</i>

88
00:10:23,471 --> 00:10:25,997
<i>Sing! Sing!</i>

89
00:10:25,997 --> 00:10:28,581
<i>Sing! Sing!</i>

90
00:10:28,581 --> 00:10:30,634
<i>Give a big hand!</i>

91
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:59,201
[Chu Sang Ah After Tax Evasion Scandal]

92
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:18,591
I told you not to watch that.

93
00:11:18,591 --> 00:11:20,241
Mi Soon.

94
00:11:20,241 --> 00:11:22,145
Yes?

95
00:11:22,145 --> 00:11:25,401
Is the person who filmed and
posted that video the problem?

96
00:11:25,401 --> 00:11:29,561
Or the people next to them
bluntly calling it out?

97
00:11:31,407 --> 00:11:34,318
Or is the problem me, a has-been past my prime?

98
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,466
Come on, of course not.

99
00:11:36,466 --> 00:11:39,949
- Past your prime? Don't say that.
- Then what, ancient?

100
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,744
You're kidding, right?

101
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:49,545
Look at these fine lines.

102
00:11:49,545 --> 00:11:50,762
Touch this up for me.

103
00:11:50,762 --> 00:11:53,135
Today my makeup has to look natural.

104
00:11:53,135 --> 00:11:55,328
Okay?

105
00:11:58,013 --> 00:12:04,098
<i>♪ The moment you stood by my side ♪</i>

106
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:08,937
<i>♪ I love that look in your eyes ♪</i>

107
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:14,150
<i>♪ Yesterday I cried ♪</i>

108
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:16,027
<i>♪ But today, because of you ♪</i>

109
00:12:16,027 --> 00:12:17,695
<i>♪ tomorrow I'll be happy ♪</i>

110
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,902
- I'll be happy!
- I'll be happy!

111
00:12:22,321 --> 00:12:27,651
<i>♪ Eat plenty today and have a drink ♪</i>

112
00:12:27,651 --> 00:12:31,910
<i>♪ All I ever needed was a gentle love ♪</i>

113
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:41,425
<i>♪ So I could forget all the years gone by ♪</i>

114
00:12:41,425 --> 00:12:43,569
<i>♪ Without you ♪</i>

115
00:12:43,569 --> 00:12:48,603
<i>♪ I can't do anything anymore ♪</i>

116
00:12:48,603 --> 00:12:53,329
<i>♪ All I know is love ♪</i>

117
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:57,545
[Assemblymember Kwak Jung Ja]

118
00:13:00,296 --> 00:13:02,927
Let me first offer my sincere birthday wishes

119
00:13:02,927 --> 00:13:06,646
to our beloved Changjo Party's
Assemblywoman Kwak Jung Ja.

120
00:13:06,646 --> 00:13:07,890
I couldn't just pass by,

121
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:10,876
so I stopped in for a moment
while I was next door.

122
00:13:10,876 --> 00:13:13,116
I'm Bang Tae Seop, the star prosecutor of

123
00:13:13,116 --> 00:13:15,676
Seoul Central District Prosecutors' Office,
Criminal Division 3.

124
00:13:15,676 --> 00:13:18,076
Thank you.

125
00:13:22,896 --> 00:13:25,480
Prosecutor Bang,
you should pour me a drink before you go.

126
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,893
Of course.

127
00:13:26,893 --> 00:13:30,213
Let me pour you a nice strong one.

128
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:41,303
He's good.

129
00:13:41,303 --> 00:13:44,536
Happy birthday.

130
00:13:45,762 --> 00:13:49,636
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

131
00:14:14,896 --> 00:14:16,128
[Stay strong today and tomorrow, too.]

132
00:14:16,128 --> 00:14:20,036
Top stars always fade eventually.

133
00:14:20,777 --> 00:14:25,120
And now that the perks he enjoyed
thanks to his wife have run out,

134
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:28,480
he probably doesn't see a future
in this office and wants out.

135
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:33,246
Yeah, I'm getting out of
the District Prosecutors' Office.

136
00:14:35,613 --> 00:14:37,359
So,

137
00:14:37,359 --> 00:14:39,729
what exactly are you planning to do?

138
00:14:39,729 --> 00:14:44,169
If you roll and crawl your way somewhere
only to find it's a sewer,

139
00:14:44,169 --> 00:14:46,819
then you find another hole to crawl into.

140
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:48,519
Fair enough.

141
00:14:48,519 --> 00:14:52,355
You got an offer
from the Changjo Party before, right?

142
00:14:52,355 --> 00:14:54,233
Instead of rotting away here,

143
00:14:54,233 --> 00:14:58,200
try getting nominated
for this year's general election.

144
00:15:01,342 --> 00:15:03,126
<i>As the general election is three months away</i>

145
00:15:03,126 --> 00:15:04,675
<i>and the presidential election
just over a year out,</i>

146
00:15:04,675 --> 00:15:08,296
<i>attention is focused on the next moves of
Mayor of Seoam, Nam Hye Hoon.</i>

147
00:15:08,296 --> 00:15:10,990
<i>She continues to lead in polls
measuring public support</i>

148
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:13,813
<i>for the opposition's next political leader.</i>

149
00:15:13,813 --> 00:15:16,403
<i>She recently gave an exclusive interview
to The London Times,</i>

150
00:15:16,403 --> 00:15:19,523
<i>the first ever by Mayor of Seoam,</i>

151
00:15:19,523 --> 00:15:22,387
<i>showcasing her presence as a global leader.</i>

152
00:15:22,387 --> 00:15:24,411
Nam Hye Hoon.

153
00:15:24,411 --> 00:15:27,168
What if she actually makes it
to the Blue House at this rate?

154
00:15:27,168 --> 00:15:28,755
Hey.

155
00:15:28,755 --> 00:15:31,219
You do know she's a sewer, right?

156
00:15:31,219 --> 00:15:33,933
Don't say something so horrifying.

157
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,215
About Senior Prosecutor Yoon...

158
00:15:35,215 --> 00:15:38,356
You know he got cut off
while digging into her, right?

159
00:15:38,356 --> 00:15:40,626
- Did he?
- Yeah.

160
00:15:40,626 --> 00:15:44,485
The case where Mayor Nam took kickbacks from TM
and pushed through that redevelopment deal.

161
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,477
He was digging into it and
got caught by the Chief Prosecutor.

162
00:15:46,477 --> 00:15:48,526
That's when his head rolled.

163
00:15:48,526 --> 00:15:51,629
Mayor Nam is the Chief Prosecutor's in-law.

164
00:15:51,629 --> 00:15:53,503
Darn it.

165
00:15:53,503 --> 00:15:56,127
But Joong Hyuk
was in the Chief Prosecutor's line.

166
00:15:56,127 --> 00:15:58,780
Line or not, he still got thrown under the bus.

167
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:00,804
Anyway, Mayor Nam

168
00:16:00,804 --> 00:16:02,628
is a hot potato right now.

169
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,255
Everyone thinks if they dig up something
and blow it open,

170
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:05,716
they'll get the spotlight

171
00:16:05,716 --> 00:16:07,961
and land a job at a big law firm
or go into politics.

172
00:16:07,961 --> 00:16:09,994
But they all jump in,

173
00:16:09,994 --> 00:16:12,119
get crushed, get blacklisted,

174
00:16:12,119 --> 00:16:15,160
and end up doing public defense
for the rest of their lives.

175
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:18,519
It's a poisoned chalice.

176
00:16:33,863 --> 00:16:35,374
Hey, it's been a while.

177
00:16:35,374 --> 00:16:37,827
Hello, Mi Soon.

178
00:16:37,827 --> 00:16:39,278
Nice haircut.

179
00:16:39,278 --> 00:16:40,987
You have a good sense, as always.

180
00:16:40,987 --> 00:16:42,977
Good work today, Mi Soon.

181
00:16:42,977 --> 00:16:44,744
Good night.

182
00:16:44,744 --> 00:16:46,268
Thought you had a team dinner.

183
00:16:46,268 --> 00:16:49,004
You're back early.

184
00:16:49,004 --> 00:16:52,504
I came early because
I wanted another drink with you.

185
00:16:52,504 --> 00:16:54,324
Got plans?

186
00:16:54,324 --> 00:16:57,984
Yeah. Something came up.

187
00:17:00,837 --> 00:17:02,888
What's with you?

188
00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:04,211
Meeting a guy?

189
00:17:04,211 --> 00:17:08,495
If you are, shouldn't you change
your underwear first?

190
00:17:08,495 --> 00:17:10,605
Must be something important.

191
00:17:10,605 --> 00:17:11,942
A film company.

192
00:17:11,942 --> 00:17:14,911
I have a script meeting.

193
00:17:17,768 --> 00:17:20,888
Doesn't sound like a film company.

194
00:17:21,607 --> 00:17:26,301
You know I have to show up sometimes,
even when I don't want to.

195
00:17:26,301 --> 00:17:29,774
So I'd appreciate it if you stopped asking.

196
00:17:33,168 --> 00:17:35,714
Okay.

197
00:17:37,535 --> 00:17:40,181
Sorry.

198
00:17:45,305 --> 00:17:48,058
Yeah, I'm heading out now.

199
00:17:51,017 --> 00:17:54,063
- Let's talk later.
- Okay.

200
00:18:18,356 --> 00:18:22,575
[The Nam Hye Hoon List]

201
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:26,117
[Social Media Chat Analysis Report]

202
00:18:31,792 --> 00:18:35,203
[Receipt for Full Payment of Property Purchase]

203
00:18:35,203 --> 00:18:36,889
[Response to Request for
Access to Personal Information]

204
00:18:36,889 --> 00:18:39,026
<i>Nam Hye Hoon's image was in free fall</i>

205
00:18:39,026 --> 00:18:42,412
<i>because of slush funds
and real estate speculation...</i>

206
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:43,331
[Suspected Backdoor Ties
Between Mayor Nam and WR Group]

207
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:45,663
<i>But after teaming up with WR recently,</i>

208
00:18:45,663 --> 00:18:49,296
<i>she suddenly rose
as a leading presidential contender.</i>

209
00:18:50,676 --> 00:18:53,856
<i>Especially... Lee Yang Mi.</i>

210
00:18:53,856 --> 00:18:56,081
<i>Who's the real power at WR these days?</i>

211
00:18:56,081 --> 00:18:57,585
[WR Group Owner Kwon Se Myeong and His Wife,
Lee Yang Mi: Korea's No. 3 Conglomerate]

212
00:18:57,585 --> 00:19:00,558
<i>It's Lee Yang Mi.</i>

213
00:19:06,836 --> 00:19:09,715
[Sansugapsan]
Excuse me, do you have a table?

214
00:19:09,715 --> 00:19:11,739
Sorry, we're closed today.

215
00:19:11,739 --> 00:19:12,824
What?

216
00:19:12,824 --> 00:19:14,541
But it's not your day off.

217
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:17,318
- Did someone rent out the whole place?
- Yes, they did.

218
00:19:17,318 --> 00:19:18,955
- What?
- I'm sorry.

219
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:20,076
Let's go somewhere else.

220
00:19:20,076 --> 00:19:22,528
- Sorry about that.
- Okay.

221
00:19:34,802 --> 00:19:37,521
How's the atmosphere on set?

222
00:19:37,521 --> 00:19:40,228
You're doing well, right?

223
00:19:40,954 --> 00:19:42,811
Even if the director's a nobody,

224
00:19:42,811 --> 00:19:44,148
I read the script myself.

225
00:19:44,148 --> 00:19:46,948
It won't flop.

226
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:50,368
Of course.

227
00:19:50,368 --> 00:19:54,308
It's my comeback project,
and you were the one who introduced it.

228
00:19:54,308 --> 00:19:57,188
I'll give it my all.

229
00:20:00,995 --> 00:20:02,939
Right.

230
00:20:02,939 --> 00:20:05,992
If you're born an actor
and will die an actor anyway,

231
00:20:05,992 --> 00:20:08,029
you've got to stay cool

232
00:20:08,029 --> 00:20:09,566
about a fate that swings like Tesla stock

233
00:20:09,566 --> 00:20:13,275
if you want to last in the long run.

234
00:20:16,124 --> 00:20:18,175
True.

235
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:20,033
I tell myself it's all part of life's lessons

236
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:23,554
and try not to ride the highs and lows...

237
00:20:23,554 --> 00:20:26,618
but in this industry,
that's easier said than done.

238
00:20:26,618 --> 00:20:28,448
Then again,

239
00:20:28,448 --> 00:20:31,675
I never liked the fate of entertainers
getting swept up by trends,

240
00:20:31,675 --> 00:20:35,365
living and dying by every rise and fall.

241
00:20:35,365 --> 00:20:36,750
With this face,

242
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:40,750
I gave up on becoming an actress pretty early.

243
00:20:41,883 --> 00:20:43,808
I'm a Scorpio,

244
00:20:43,808 --> 00:20:48,514
so I prefer pulling the strings,
not being pulled.

245
00:20:52,910 --> 00:20:54,273
And you...

246
00:20:54,273 --> 00:20:58,813
Before you crashed,
you stayed on top thanks to me.

247
00:21:01,912 --> 00:21:06,392
Anyway, I've bought shares in your agency,

248
00:21:06,392 --> 00:21:09,918
and you're not getting any younger.

249
00:21:09,918 --> 00:21:13,971
Did you really think
I'd just let you fade away like this?

250
00:21:27,611 --> 00:21:30,604
So...

251
00:21:30,604 --> 00:21:31,707
I do have one card

252
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:34,217
that could put you right back
on top in one shot.

253
00:21:34,217 --> 00:21:36,075
Lee Yang Mi...

254
00:21:36,075 --> 00:21:37,953
[Growing Favoritism Allegations]
<i>She's the one who stirred things up</i>

255
00:21:37,953 --> 00:21:40,023
<i>with the Chief Prosecutor
and got me forced out.</i>

256
00:21:40,023 --> 00:21:42,129
<i>Mayor Nam's approval ratings were dropping,</i>

257
00:21:42,129 --> 00:21:43,752
<i>but her image turned around</i>

258
00:21:43,752 --> 00:21:45,782
<i>right after she started appearing
with Lee Yang Mi,</i>

259
00:21:45,782 --> 00:21:49,055
<i>the one who pulls the strings in the media.</i>

260
00:21:49,801 --> 00:21:51,852
I knew she was bankrolling films and dramas

261
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:55,940
and meeting celebrities through that,

262
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:58,246
but I didn't realize her reach
extended into politics too.

263
00:21:58,246 --> 00:22:01,159
<i>Exactly.</i>

264
00:22:01,159 --> 00:22:04,356
So someone like Lee Yang Mi chose Nam Hye Hoon

265
00:22:04,356 --> 00:22:06,754
as her presidential partner?

266
00:22:06,754 --> 00:22:08,897
<i>Yeah.</i>

267
00:22:09,522 --> 00:22:13,693
<i>But apparently she has a certain way
of doing business in politics.</i>

268
00:22:13,693 --> 00:22:16,498
<i>She brings in celebrities she has leverage over</i>

269
00:22:16,498 --> 00:22:20,463
<i>and uses them for sexual favors.</i>

270
00:22:22,276 --> 00:22:24,207
Sang Ah.

271
00:22:24,207 --> 00:22:29,420
That rising actor your agency signed
with CEO Eom.

272
00:22:30,715 --> 00:22:33,375
Bae Yun Seong.

273
00:22:33,375 --> 00:22:35,125
Mayor Nam says

274
00:22:35,125 --> 00:22:38,415
watching his drama these days
is the highlight of her day.

275
00:22:38,415 --> 00:22:42,722
She keeps saying she wants to meet him.

276
00:22:42,722 --> 00:22:44,471
You know...

277
00:22:44,471 --> 00:22:46,615
We signed up for treatments
at Director Park's aesthetic clinic,

278
00:22:46,615 --> 00:22:47,963
and guess what.

279
00:22:47,963 --> 00:22:51,406
She wrote her nickname down as "Kim Byul."

280
00:22:51,406 --> 00:22:53,792
Funny, right?

281
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:59,033
That's the name of
Yun Seong's co-star, isn't it?

282
00:23:07,025 --> 00:23:09,732
It is, right?

283
00:23:10,752 --> 00:23:13,838
- Director...
- Or am I wrong?

284
00:23:14,731 --> 00:23:17,958
Don't go that far.

285
00:23:19,326 --> 00:23:20,843
What?

286
00:23:20,843 --> 00:23:23,503
You should be satisfied with just me.

287
00:23:23,503 --> 00:23:26,849
Leave the agency and Yun Seong out of it.

288
00:23:30,884 --> 00:23:33,744
Listen, Chu Sang Ah.

289
00:23:34,678 --> 00:23:37,557
Get a grip.

290
00:23:40,812 --> 00:23:43,262
You're not stupid.

291
00:23:43,262 --> 00:23:46,881
You said you wanted your top spot back.

292
00:23:46,881 --> 00:23:49,912
Whether you sink lower or climb back up
depends on me.

293
00:23:49,912 --> 00:23:52,938
So face reality.

294
00:23:52,938 --> 00:23:55,225
In a situation like this...

295
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:58,998
This isn't the time
to be clinging to your pride.

296
00:24:06,277 --> 00:24:10,781
If you take one more step, it is a cliff.

297
00:24:10,781 --> 00:24:12,585
You see that, right?

298
00:24:12,585 --> 00:24:14,302
Whether you keep going or not...

299
00:24:14,302 --> 00:24:17,201
That's your call.

300
00:24:32,809 --> 00:24:35,682
Did you drink a lot?

301
00:24:36,983 --> 00:24:39,470
No.

302
00:24:39,470 --> 00:24:42,129
I think I just feel sick.

303
00:24:44,476 --> 00:24:47,156
Did something happen?

304
00:24:47,156 --> 00:24:50,056
Just a little rough.

305
00:24:59,446 --> 00:25:02,206
Are we...

306
00:25:02,206 --> 00:25:05,119
going to be okay?

307
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:22,768
I'm sorry.

308
00:25:24,542 --> 00:25:28,442
I feel like I'm not much help to you.

309
00:25:32,682 --> 00:25:35,915
Don't say that.

310
00:25:38,505 --> 00:25:41,645
Honestly, today was hard.

311
00:25:43,432 --> 00:25:47,178
I know I can go further,

312
00:25:49,025 --> 00:25:51,744
but I'm scared

313
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:56,071
this might be the end for me.

314
00:26:04,698 --> 00:26:06,815
Do you know why

315
00:26:06,815 --> 00:26:10,001
I wanted to be with you so badly?

316
00:26:10,962 --> 00:26:14,852
Even when you get hurt and knocked down,

317
00:26:14,852 --> 00:26:18,058
even when you're afraid,

318
00:26:18,832 --> 00:26:22,132
you're the kind of woman

319
00:26:22,132 --> 00:26:25,858
who's more afraid of stopping
than anything else.

320
00:26:26,604 --> 00:26:29,112
That's what I admired

321
00:26:29,112 --> 00:26:31,745
about you.

322
00:26:42,913 --> 00:26:45,813
I feel the same.

323
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:49,167
With you...

324
00:26:49,167 --> 00:26:52,966
I thought I could go all the way.

325
00:26:53,846 --> 00:26:56,553
That's why.

326
00:27:10,704 --> 00:27:13,497
You know, I threw up.

327
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:03,704
When I look at the woman,
it feels like I'm looking at myself.

328
00:28:03,704 --> 00:28:06,598
That's why I wanted to have her.

329
00:28:06,598 --> 00:28:10,378
And I thought I did...

330
00:28:10,378 --> 00:28:12,758
But lately,

331
00:28:12,758 --> 00:28:16,404
I'm starting to think
maybe that was just my illusion.

332
00:28:17,191 --> 00:28:20,110
You're madly in love with her.

333
00:28:21,821 --> 00:28:24,119
This isn't the place

334
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:27,794
to go on about your tragic love story.

335
00:28:29,199 --> 00:28:32,482
I don't have anywhere else
to talk about my wife.

336
00:28:32,482 --> 00:28:34,768
Sorry.

337
00:28:35,962 --> 00:28:39,015
No need to apologize.

338
00:28:39,015 --> 00:28:43,408
These are files on Lee Yang Mi
and Nam Hye Hoon.

339
00:28:46,053 --> 00:28:48,696
They really are close.

340
00:28:48,696 --> 00:28:49,993
Even with their busy schedules,

341
00:28:49,993 --> 00:28:52,066
whether it's golf or the aesthetic clinic...

342
00:28:52,066 --> 00:28:55,106
they always show up together.

343
00:28:55,952 --> 00:28:57,723
And...

344
00:28:57,723 --> 00:28:59,808
the SBC vice chairman
and the Doyak Party leader

345
00:28:59,808 --> 00:29:01,708
arrived one after another,

346
00:29:01,708 --> 00:29:04,659
took the elevator up,
and got off at the penthouse floor.

347
00:29:04,659 --> 00:29:06,376
Soon after, a group of women arrived

348
00:29:06,376 --> 00:29:08,109
and got off on the same floor.

349
00:29:08,109 --> 00:29:11,589
I couldn't get a clear look,

350
00:29:11,589 --> 00:29:15,149
but they looked like recognizable celebrities.

351
00:29:16,462 --> 00:29:18,553
Interesting.

352
00:29:18,553 --> 00:29:21,379
And this is

353
00:29:22,079 --> 00:29:24,376
the WR Hotel reservation list.

354
00:29:24,376 --> 00:29:26,316
[Hotel Room Reservation Log]
See the name "Kim Byul?"

355
00:29:26,316 --> 00:29:29,320
That's the name Nam Hye Hoon uses
when she books aesthetic appointments.

356
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:32,320
Next Wednesday.

357
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:34,560
Okay.

358
00:29:37,820 --> 00:29:39,790
This case...

359
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:41,461
Finish it well.

360
00:29:41,461 --> 00:29:45,446
Once it's done, I'll throw in a little extra.

361
00:30:00,321 --> 00:30:02,958
Looks like you're really quitting your job.

362
00:30:02,958 --> 00:30:06,346
You should stop playing informant for me too.

363
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:09,592
I'll find you something else.

364
00:30:10,978 --> 00:30:14,676
I'll handle my own life, so stay out of it.

365
00:30:14,676 --> 00:30:18,386
How am I supposed to stay out of your life?

366
00:30:18,386 --> 00:30:19,837
If you can't...

367
00:30:19,837 --> 00:30:22,347
It's not like you'd choose me over Chu Sang Ah.

368
00:30:22,347 --> 00:30:24,753
I'm heading out.

369
00:30:39,713 --> 00:30:42,509
[CINE24]

370
00:30:47,252 --> 00:30:48,628
Tae Seop.

371
00:30:48,628 --> 00:30:49,882
Yes, sir.

372
00:30:49,882 --> 00:30:51,167
I hear

373
00:30:51,167 --> 00:30:53,401
you've been making quite a name
for yourself lately.

374
00:30:53,401 --> 00:30:55,334
Sorry?

375
00:31:00,586 --> 00:31:03,499
Word is you've been sticking your nose

376
00:31:03,499 --> 00:31:07,709
where it doesn't belong.

377
00:31:07,709 --> 00:31:12,035
Decided to start living life on the edge?

378
00:31:13,934 --> 00:31:16,567
Mayor Nam Hye Hoon.

379
00:31:16,567 --> 00:31:19,787
I hear you've been digging into her lately.

380
00:31:19,787 --> 00:31:21,671
Oh, that's just...

381
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:23,065
You little punk!

382
00:31:23,065 --> 00:31:25,090
If I miss that deputy chief promotion again,

383
00:31:25,090 --> 00:31:28,757
are you going to take responsibility for it?

384
00:31:28,757 --> 00:31:31,042
What on earth are you doing?

385
00:31:31,042 --> 00:31:32,633
The personnel announcement is coming up.

386
00:31:32,633 --> 00:31:36,003
Are you trying to drag us all down with you?

387
00:31:36,003 --> 00:31:37,613
Listen.

388
00:31:37,613 --> 00:31:39,534
If you want to get yourself killed,
do it alone.

389
00:31:39,534 --> 00:31:42,420
Why are you splashing your mess all over me?

390
00:31:42,420 --> 00:31:44,444
Sir, this is a misunderstanding.

391
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:46,834
I was only checking something I heard.

392
00:31:46,834 --> 00:31:48,684
Checking?

393
00:31:48,684 --> 00:31:50,457
You little jerk...

394
00:31:50,457 --> 00:31:52,370
Hey.

395
00:31:52,370 --> 00:31:55,241
Who do you think you are,
checking up on Mayor Nam?

396
00:31:55,241 --> 00:31:56,685
Why? Why?

397
00:31:56,685 --> 00:31:59,118
Darn it.

398
00:32:00,475 --> 00:32:03,175
This is really irritating.

399
00:32:17,123 --> 00:32:20,381
<i>Even this bastard's cousin is a congressman.</i>

400
00:32:20,381 --> 00:32:22,057
<i>If the prosecution gets purged,</i>

401
00:32:22,057 --> 00:32:24,651
<i>guys like me will be the first to go.</i>

402
00:32:24,651 --> 00:32:27,468
Drop the Mayor Nam case right now.

403
00:32:27,468 --> 00:32:29,038
Got it?

404
00:32:29,038 --> 00:32:30,669
Of course. Much respect, sir.

405
00:32:30,669 --> 00:32:32,721
Darn it.

406
00:32:37,227 --> 00:32:39,674
<i>That's not going to...</i>

407
00:32:39,674 --> 00:32:41,793
<i>work for me.</i>

408
00:32:45,099 --> 00:32:47,730
<i>My way out is already gone,</i>

409
00:32:47,730 --> 00:32:51,390
<i>so I might as well go all in.</i>

410
00:33:18,121 --> 00:33:22,075
I heard they call you the Doberman of
the Seoam Central District Prosecution.

411
00:33:22,075 --> 00:33:25,162
I actually keep a Doberman myself.

412
00:33:26,795 --> 00:33:30,168
Is that why you went after Chu Sang Ah too?

413
00:33:30,995 --> 00:33:34,049
I can't exactly deny that.

414
00:33:34,049 --> 00:33:35,726
Go ahead.

415
00:33:35,726 --> 00:33:38,426
I'm on a diet.

416
00:33:48,907 --> 00:33:50,204
<i>Kwon Jong Uk.</i>

417
00:33:50,204 --> 00:33:52,134
<i>The heir to WR Group,</i>

418
00:33:52,134 --> 00:33:54,354
<i>the third-largest company
in Korea by market cap.</i>

419
00:33:54,354 --> 00:33:56,551
<i>He's been raised with a silver spoon.</i>

420
00:33:56,551 --> 00:34:00,984
<i>All pride and not a shred of common sense.</i>

421
00:34:00,984 --> 00:34:02,975
<i>Kwon Se Myeong, the owner of WR,</i>

422
00:34:02,975 --> 00:34:04,876
<i>and his wife, Director Lee Yang Mi.</i>

423
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:06,226
<i>Then there are the twin sons</i>

424
00:34:06,226 --> 00:34:07,773
<i>from Kwon Se Myeong's previous marriage.</i>

425
00:34:07,773 --> 00:34:10,215
<i>Kwon Jong Uk and Kwon Jong Il.</i>

426
00:34:10,215 --> 00:34:12,758
<i>When the younger brother, Kwon Jong Il,
gave up his claim to management,</i>

427
00:34:12,758 --> 00:34:16,133
<i>WR was practically Jong Uk's for the taking.</i>

428
00:34:16,133 --> 00:34:18,470
<i>But then Lee Yang Mi gave birth
to Kwon Se Myeong's daughter.</i>

429
00:34:18,470 --> 00:34:20,781
<i>She secured control of the hotel
and entertainment divisions,</i>

430
00:34:20,781 --> 00:34:25,861
<i>and that is when the real war
between her and Kwon Jong Uk began.</i>

431
00:34:25,861 --> 00:34:28,474
<i>So far, the score is two to one.</i>

432
00:34:28,474 --> 00:34:30,171
<i>Lee Yang Mi is the one with two.</i>

433
00:34:30,171 --> 00:34:33,348
<i>Which means if I take down Nam Hye Hoon
and it hits Lee Yang Mi as well,</i>

434
00:34:33,348 --> 00:34:35,165
<i>the one who benefits the most</i>

435
00:34:35,165 --> 00:34:36,362
<i>is this man.</i>

436
00:34:36,362 --> 00:34:40,852
It sounded like an interesting offer,
so I came.

437
00:34:40,852 --> 00:34:43,222
But how exactly are you planning

438
00:34:43,222 --> 00:34:46,855
to take down Lee Yang Mi through Nam Hye Hoon?

439
00:34:48,202 --> 00:34:49,973
Soon, Lee Yang Mi will be making

440
00:34:49,973 --> 00:34:53,906
an illegal lobbying move on
Mayor Nam at the WR Hotel.

441
00:34:54,797 --> 00:34:58,702
I'll raid the scene and take Mayor Nam down.

442
00:34:58,702 --> 00:35:02,508
When that happens,
Lee Yang Mi's grand plan falls apart too.

443
00:35:07,425 --> 00:35:09,945
That is sexy.

444
00:35:13,741 --> 00:35:17,827
So you must want something from me
for coming all this way.

445
00:35:23,823 --> 00:35:28,180
Make sure the story breaks
and does not get buried.

446
00:35:28,180 --> 00:35:31,470
And back me for the nomination
in the upcoming general election.

447
00:35:31,470 --> 00:35:34,077
You want my backing?

448
00:35:34,077 --> 00:35:35,774
That's not hard.

449
00:35:35,774 --> 00:35:37,894
But,

450
00:35:39,014 --> 00:35:41,680
we just met.

451
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:45,226
Why should I trust you?

452
00:35:46,714 --> 00:35:49,378
I never asked you to trust me.

453
00:35:49,378 --> 00:35:52,839
You need Lee Yang Mi taken down
without getting blood on your hands

454
00:35:52,839 --> 00:35:54,511
if you want to protect WR.

455
00:35:54,511 --> 00:35:56,328
And I need Mayor Nam taken down

456
00:35:56,328 --> 00:35:58,978
to clear my path to the general election.

457
00:35:58,978 --> 00:36:00,122
Is there

458
00:36:00,122 --> 00:36:01,908
any bond stronger than

459
00:36:01,908 --> 00:36:04,888
two people whose interests align?

460
00:36:07,657 --> 00:36:10,340
You and I...

461
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:12,517
see the world the same way.

462
00:36:12,517 --> 00:36:15,450
You're a strategist, huh?

463
00:36:16,750 --> 00:36:19,754
Seems like a waste to stop
at the general election with you.

464
00:36:19,754 --> 00:36:21,778
The general election is not my goal.

465
00:36:21,778 --> 00:36:25,847
My goal is to stand at the top of Korea.

466
00:36:34,707 --> 00:36:36,624
Now that is some ambition.

467
00:36:36,624 --> 00:36:38,868
Protect WR Group.

468
00:36:38,868 --> 00:36:42,148
And keep working with me.

469
00:36:45,155 --> 00:36:47,562
Bravo.

470
00:36:56,890 --> 00:37:00,736
I heard you met Director Lee Yang Mi.

471
00:37:04,146 --> 00:37:06,159
Yeah.

472
00:37:08,146 --> 00:37:10,457
Then I guess you heard about

473
00:37:10,457 --> 00:37:13,257
Yun Seong too.

474
00:37:14,941 --> 00:37:16,636
How did you know?

475
00:37:16,636 --> 00:37:20,204
WR's director office contacted us.

476
00:37:24,136 --> 00:37:26,160
Don't worry about it.

477
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:28,510
It is nothing like that.

478
00:37:28,510 --> 00:37:30,930
I expected something like this

479
00:37:30,930 --> 00:37:34,750
when Director Lee bought shares
in our company.

480
00:37:35,994 --> 00:37:39,381
This really sucks.

481
00:37:40,615 --> 00:37:43,415
Yeah, it does.

482
00:37:46,141 --> 00:37:48,327
<i>By the way,</i>

483
00:37:48,327 --> 00:37:52,187
<i>do you know why I bought shares in your agency?</i>

484
00:37:52,187 --> 00:37:54,594
<i>What, because I felt sorry for you?</i>

485
00:37:54,594 --> 00:37:56,540
<i>No.</i>

486
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:58,677
<i>I'm not a charity worker.</i>

487
00:37:58,677 --> 00:38:00,701
<i>I'm a businesswoman.</i>

488
00:38:00,701 --> 00:38:03,091
<i>Do you think I'd invest that kind of money</i>

489
00:38:03,091 --> 00:38:05,784
<i>without anything to gain?</i>

490
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:07,481
<i>Are you threatening me right now?</i>

491
00:38:07,481 --> 00:38:09,510
<i>I'm offering you a deal.</i>

492
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:12,544
<i>Let's call it even with this.</i>

493
00:38:14,051 --> 00:38:19,428
<i>Whether you end up shredded
in my blender as the sacrificial lamb,</i>

494
00:38:19,428 --> 00:38:22,758
<i>or survive and step back onto the stage,</i>

495
00:38:22,758 --> 00:38:26,058
<i>that's entirely up to you.</i>

496
00:38:32,603 --> 00:38:34,547
<i>Oh, if that sounded like a threat,</i>

497
00:38:34,547 --> 00:38:36,807
<i>sorry.</i>

498
00:38:51,062 --> 00:38:53,921
Let's find another way.

499
00:38:55,823 --> 00:38:59,366
I can't make a comeback using
a dirty trick like that.

500
00:38:59,366 --> 00:39:04,579
And Yun Seong will become a star soon anyway.

501
00:39:06,776 --> 00:39:09,680
So even if Lee Yang Mi's side reaches out,

502
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:12,993
don't touch Yun Seong.

503
00:39:15,016 --> 00:39:17,735
Understood?

504
00:39:19,649 --> 00:39:22,487
All right.

505
00:39:35,678 --> 00:39:38,491
Hello, director.

506
00:39:39,551 --> 00:39:41,045
Hey, leave that.

507
00:39:41,045 --> 00:39:42,998
The energy is off today.
That color works better.

508
00:39:42,998 --> 00:39:45,284
Understood.

509
00:39:50,491 --> 00:39:52,208
This scent doesn't suit the lobby today.

510
00:39:52,208 --> 00:39:53,448
Then...

511
00:39:53,448 --> 00:39:55,473
which scent would you prefer?

512
00:39:55,473 --> 00:39:58,818
Patchouli's woody note adds
a more refined mood,

513
00:39:58,818 --> 00:40:02,991
and the warm trail of ambergris
gives it a sensual finish.

514
00:40:02,991 --> 00:40:05,376
Clear that one out.

515
00:40:05,376 --> 00:40:08,563
Who is this VVIP coming today?

516
00:40:08,563 --> 00:40:11,082
The mayor.

517
00:40:11,942 --> 00:40:13,666
Welcome, ma'am.

518
00:40:13,666 --> 00:40:16,342
- Yeah.
- This way, please.

519
00:40:43,257 --> 00:40:48,497
<i>Whether you end up shredded
in my blender as the sacrificial lamb,</i>

520
00:40:48,497 --> 00:40:51,634
<i>or survive and step back onto the stage,</i>

521
00:40:51,634 --> 00:40:54,847
<i>that's entirely up to you.</i>

522
00:40:54,847 --> 00:40:56,916
Sang Ah.

523
00:41:00,433 --> 00:41:03,436
I was supposed to meet CEO Eom. Where is he?

524
00:41:03,436 --> 00:41:04,920
Well... about that...

525
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,756
He said something suddenly came up.

526
00:41:07,756 --> 00:41:10,202
What do you mean?

527
00:41:31,344 --> 00:41:32,414
Hey, Sang Ah.

528
00:41:32,414 --> 00:41:33,560
Where are you?

529
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:35,571
<i>I'm just...</i>

530
00:41:35,571 --> 00:41:37,990
Well...

531
00:41:37,990 --> 00:41:41,221
I didn't want to do this either.

532
00:41:41,221 --> 00:41:42,431
<i>But</i>

533
00:41:42,431 --> 00:41:43,648
<i>Director Lee's office...</i>

534
00:41:43,648 --> 00:41:46,478
They are coming down hard,
saying they will pull their investment.

535
00:41:46,478 --> 00:41:48,555
Our company is already
struggling as it is, you know.

536
00:41:48,555 --> 00:41:50,052
<i>Are you insane?</i>

537
00:41:50,052 --> 00:41:52,925
You still can't go through with this.

538
00:41:52,925 --> 00:41:55,009
What did Yun Seong ever do wrong?

539
00:41:55,009 --> 00:41:58,266
He agreed to it.

540
00:41:58,266 --> 00:41:59,293
What?

541
00:41:59,293 --> 00:42:00,953
<i>Yun Seong said</i>

542
00:42:00,953 --> 00:42:04,743
<i>there is a limit to the roles he can land
through auditions.</i>

543
00:42:04,743 --> 00:42:05,861
<i>And once this is over,</i>

544
00:42:05,861 --> 00:42:09,737
WR will cast him as the lead
in a romcom they're producing.

545
00:42:09,737 --> 00:42:12,324
So yeah, Yun Seong was the one
who said he'd do it first.

546
00:42:13,066 --> 00:42:15,024
<i>Don't worry.</i>

547
00:42:15,024 --> 00:42:18,310
<i>He is ambitious, you know.</i>

548
00:42:22,564 --> 00:42:24,061
Let's go to the WR Hotel.

549
00:42:24,061 --> 00:42:26,004
Yes.

550
00:42:30,108 --> 00:42:32,078
Today's recommendation is

551
00:42:32,078 --> 00:42:34,661
a premium vintage from Lafano Winery.

552
00:42:34,661 --> 00:42:38,694
It has a spicy profile with a firm, full body.

553
00:42:46,186 --> 00:42:48,986
Enjoy your evening.

554
00:43:41,523 --> 00:43:43,807
[Bae Yun Seong]

555
00:43:47,461 --> 00:43:50,385
<i>The call can't be completed. Please leave...</i>

556
00:45:14,208 --> 00:45:17,988
<i>Penthouse, 17th floor. Target is in.</i>

557
00:46:43,454 --> 00:46:45,685
I'm by the back entrance...

558
00:46:45,685 --> 00:46:48,958
Chu Sang Ah is here.

559
00:46:49,584 --> 00:46:51,996
What are you talking about?
You sure you didn't see wrong?

560
00:46:51,996 --> 00:46:53,067
No.

561
00:46:53,067 --> 00:46:56,408
You know my eyes don't miss things.

562
00:47:23,151 --> 00:47:26,010
Yun Seong.

563
00:47:26,010 --> 00:47:28,377
Sang Ah?

564
00:48:06,948 --> 00:48:09,748
<i>You have to go in, Sang Ah.</i>

565
00:48:18,425 --> 00:48:21,411
<i>All it takes is closing your eyes once,</i>

566
00:48:21,411 --> 00:48:24,658
<i>and you will be a star.</i>

567
00:49:14,146 --> 00:49:16,692
Let's go.

568
00:49:20,463 --> 00:49:22,860
I'm really sorry.

569
00:49:22,860 --> 00:49:26,340
I'll just close my eyes once and come back.

570
00:49:49,278 --> 00:49:52,877
<i>Hello, ma'am. I'm Bae Yun Seong.</i>

571
00:49:52,877 --> 00:49:54,539
<i>Oh, there you are.</i>

572
00:49:54,539 --> 00:49:58,292
<i>You're even cuter in person.</i>

573
00:49:58,292 --> 00:49:59,649
<i>Come sit here.</i>

574
00:49:59,649 --> 00:50:01,589
<i>Yes.</i>

575
00:51:05,870 --> 00:51:07,574
<i>Close your eyes</i>

576
00:51:07,574 --> 00:51:10,001
<i>just once tonight,</i>

577
00:51:10,001 --> 00:51:13,234
<i>and you'll be a star.</i>

578
00:51:41,919 --> 00:51:45,112
<i>The call can't be completed. Please leave...</i>

579
00:51:46,384 --> 00:51:50,124
[Bang Tae Seop]

580
00:53:53,799 --> 00:53:56,739
Try calling me Byul.

581
00:53:58,092 --> 00:53:59,709
Byul.

582
00:53:59,709 --> 00:54:02,429
Oh, Kim Byul.

583
00:54:13,125 --> 00:54:14,576
Kim Byul.

584
00:54:15,223 --> 00:54:17,489
Call me Byul.

585
00:54:17,489 --> 00:54:20,703
Byul... Byul...

586
00:54:22,495 --> 00:54:25,776
Hello, Mayor Nam Hye Hoon.

587
00:54:26,716 --> 00:54:29,267
What the... Who are you?

588
00:54:29,267 --> 00:54:30,704
Who are you?

589
00:54:30,704 --> 00:54:32,602
Hey!

590
00:54:32,602 --> 00:54:34,247
I'm sorry. Please let me go!

591
00:54:34,247 --> 00:54:37,563
Is anyone out there?

592
00:54:57,250 --> 00:54:59,735
[Hong Jin Kyu]
[CEO of Big Entertainment]

593
00:54:59,735 --> 00:55:03,321
[9 years earlier]

594
00:58:13,895 --> 00:58:15,639
<i>This is a good film.</i>

595
00:58:15,639 --> 00:58:17,567
<i>It's a shame it will never be released.</i>

596
00:58:17,567 --> 00:58:20,739
<i>Do you have any idea</i>

597
00:58:20,739 --> 00:58:22,234
<i>who's holding the keys right now?</i>

598
00:58:22,234 --> 00:58:24,813
<i>This was done without consulting me.</i>

599
00:58:24,813 --> 00:58:27,164
<i>That's your fault too.</i>

600
00:58:27,164 --> 00:58:31,053
<i>From now on, you work for me.</i>

601
00:58:31,053 --> 00:58:33,250
<i>Are you hiding something from me these days?</i>

602
00:58:33,250 --> 00:58:34,853
<i>No.</i>

603
00:58:34,853 --> 00:58:37,191
<i>My wife is hiding something.</i>

604
00:58:37,191 --> 00:58:39,410
<i>Wiretap her or follow her.</i>

605
00:58:39,410 --> 00:58:41,160
<i>Just dig into it for me.</i>

606
00:58:41,160 --> 00:58:42,640
<i>Please.</i>

607
00:58:42,640 --> 00:58:44,297
<i>If you go any further with this...</i>

608
00:58:44,297 --> 00:58:46,850
<i>you and I are finished.</i>

609
00:58:46,850 --> 00:58:49,787
<i>You might be opening Pandora's box.</i>

610
00:58:49,787 --> 00:58:53,140
<i>If it is a box that will be opened anyway...</i>

611
00:58:53,140 --> 00:58:56,813
<i>then it might as well be me who opens it first.</i>
